WEBVTT

00:08:57.485 --> 00:09:00.411
And their neighbor,
an Argentine kid of Italian origin

00:09:00.435 --> 00:09:02.701
named Astor Piazzolla,

00:09:02.725 --> 00:09:04.743
hears it,

00:09:04.767 --> 00:09:06.294
assimilates it

00:09:06.318 --> 00:09:09.319
and transforms the tango
of the second half of the 20th century

00:09:09.343 --> 00:09:10.496
with his ...

00:09:10.520 --> 00:09:13.623
(Counts out the beats) One two three,
one two three, one two.

00:09:14.025 --> 00:09:16.948
(Sings "Adios Nonino")

00:09:22.114 --> 00:09:26.805
He also played it on his bandoneon,
a 19th-century German instrument

00:09:26.829 --> 00:09:30.956
created for churches
that couldn't afford to buy organs,